        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: serve ClawHub docs with shared docs builder",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Replaces the copied `scripts/docs-site` renderer with a thin adapter that stages ClawHub `docs/**` into the shape expected by the shared `openclaw/docs` builder.\n- Builds generated docs into `public/docs` for the ClawHub app, with `/docs` as the base path and ClawHub docs metadata/search/Molty config.\n- Updates `docs:run` to preview the generated ClawHub docs locally and adds a ClawHub-specific docs smoke test.\n- Removes renderer-only dev dependencies from ClawHub now that those stay owned by `openclaw/docs`.\n\n## Dependency\n\n- Depends on openclaw/docs#39 for the shared builder config hooks used by this adapter.\n\n## Proof\n\n```bash\nOPENCLAW_DOCS_REPO_DIR=<openclaw/docs checkout> bun run docs:build && bun run docs:smoke && bunx vitest run scripts/docs-builder.test.mjs\n```\n\nRelevant output:\n\n```text\nrendered 15/15 per-page og cards\nbuilt 17 pages in dist/docs-site (full)\ndocs search index ok: 16 entries\nIndexed 16 pages\nClawHub docs built with openclaw/docs: public/docs\nClawHub docs smoke ok\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed (3)\n```\n\n```bash\nbun run ci:static\n```\n\nRelevant output:\n\n```text\npeer ok: @auth/core 0.37.4 satisfies @convex-dev/auth (^0.37.0)\nNo vulnerabilities found\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\n```bash\nDOCS_RUN_PORT=17654 bun run docs:run\ncurl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:17654/docs/quickstart\n```\n\nRelevant output:\n\n```text\nClawHub docs preview: http://127.0.0.1:17654/docs/\n```\n\n## Review Notes\n\n- `OPENCLAW_DOCS_REPO_REF` is honored even when a checkout already exists, so pinned builder PR/SHA testing does not silently use stale code.\n- Generated docs output remains ignored; this PR only commits source/config/script changes.\n",
